article.headline: North Texas 84, New Orleans 81
article.story: NEW ORLEANS (AP) -- Jerome Rogers and Michael Jones each hit two free throws in the final 18 seconds to give North Texas an 84-81 come-from-behind win over New Orleans Thursday night. Leonard Hopkins led the Mean Green (13-13, 8-3 Sun Belt) with 25 points, while Michael DeGrate added 20. Billy McDade led four New Orleans players in double figures, scoring 21 points. Johnell Smith had 16, Bo McCalebb added 15, Kyle Buggs had 12 and Nathaniel Parker added 12. New Orleans built its lead to as many as 16 points in second half and led 60-44 with 13:54 to play, but North Texas rallied, outscoring the Privateers 27-11 over the next nine-plus minutes.
